id: pm-todos-982k
title: "Round-trip import corrupts title + drops type ([Type] tag not parsed back)"
description: "The exporter (renderDefaultMarkdown) appends each open item's type as a trailing ' [Type]' annotation, but the importer (parseMarkdownTodos) only strips the '<!-- pm-id -->' provenance comment — never the [Type] tag. With the new --upsert (2026.6.5), re-import now MATCHES by pm-id and UPDATES the existing item, so the round-trip: (1) folds '[Type]' into the title, and (2) resets type to the global default (Task). The corruption COMPOUNDS: each export->import --upsert appends another tag ('Crash on startup' -> '[Issue]' -> '[Issue] [Task]'). Confirmed against published pm-todos@2026.6.5."
type: Issue
status: in_progress
priority: 1
tags[4]: correctness,import,round-trip,upsert
created_at: "2026-06-05T10:55:16.005Z"
updated_at: "2026-06-05T10:55:20.124Z"
author: codex
acceptance_criteria: "export -> import --upsert leaves title and type byte-identical; trailing [Type] tag parsed back into --type only when a pm-id provenance comment is present; hand-written lines ending in [foo] are untouched (default path stable); existing 52 tests still pass + new round-trip-fidelity tests added"
body: ""
